  "plainText": "Exclusive to:\nTab Icon\n“I love camping.”\n–Woodie\nSurvival Tab items and structures are generally useful things which can be Crafted from the Survival Tab shown as a snare icon on the left side of the screen. Though some such as the Trap are always available, others must be unlocked with a Science Machine, Alchemy Engine or a Blueprint.\nDownloadable Content[edit | edit source]\nIn the Reign of Giants DLC, Siesta Lean-tos, Luxury Fans, and Insulated Packs were added to the Survival Tab.\nIn the Shipwrecked DLC, Silly Monkey Balls, Tropical Parasols, Anti Venom, Thatch Packs, Palm Leaf Huts, Tropical Fans, Sea Sacks, Doydoy Nests can be crafted and while playing as Warly, Chef Pouches in the Survival Tab. This DLC also includes the Siesta Lean-to.\nIn the Hamlet DLC, Bug B'Gone repellent and the Bird Whistle can be crafted in the Survival Tab. Siesta Lean-tos and Insulated Pack are also available in this DLC.\nCraftable Items and Structures[edit | edit source]\nThe following items and structures can be crafted in the Survival Tab:\nTrap\nBird Trap\nBug Net\nFishing Rod\nPretty Parasol\nUmbrella\nHoney Poultice\nHealing Salve\nCompass\nThermal Stone\nBackpack\nPiggyback\nStraw Roll\nFur Roll\nTent\nBundling Wrap\nSiesta Lean-to\nLuxury Fan\nInsulated Pack\nAnti Venom\nTropical Parasol\nSilly Monkey Ball\nThatch Pack\nPalm Leaf Hut\nTropical Fan\nSea Sack\nChef Pouch\nDoydoy Nest\nBug B'Gone\nBird Whistle\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve Crafting Tabs\nRegular\nTools\nLight\nSurvival\nFood\nScience\nFight\nStructures\nRefine\nMagic\nDress\n(Nautical )\n(Treasure Hunting )\nCharacter-Specific\nBooks\nTinkering\n(Green Thumb )\nNon-prototypable\nAncient\nVolcanic\n(Renovate\nCity Planning )",
